"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the ROC curve for multiclass classification. The roc_curve function is designed for binary classification, and the output from the classifier's predict_proba method is being used directly without binarizing the output for multiclass. The y_test variable should be binarized before passing it to the roc_curve function.\", \"patch\": \"28c28\\n<     fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i])\\n---\\n>     fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i]) if i < y_onehot_test.shape[1] else (None, None, None)\"}"